# {Organization Name}

## Prerequisites

- Claude Code CLI
- GitHub CLI (`gh`) authenticated
- Your project's toolchain (Node.js, Python, etc.)

## Setup

```bash
# 1. Initialize your company (interactive)
claude
> /init

# Or manually:
# mkdir my-org
# cp _template/workspace-config.yaml my-org/workspace-config.yaml
# Edit my-org/workspace-config.yaml with your values

# 2. Clone project repos into your org folder
git clone git@github.com:your-org/project-a.git my-org/project-a
git clone git@github.com:your-org/project-b.git my-org/project-b

# 4. Start Polaris
claude
```

## Projects

| Project | Repo | Description |
|---------|------|-------------|
| project-a | `your-org/project-a` | Main application |
| project-b | `your-org/project-b` | Shared library |

## Team Conventions

Document your team's conventions here. These will evolve into L2 rules in `.claude/rules/company/`:

- Branch naming: `task/{TICKET-KEY}-{description}`
- PR approval threshold: 2
- Sprint capacity: 20 points
- Code review SLA: 24 hours
